            AMIGAPUNT HELP FILE!


            Introduction:

The AMIGAPUNT programs  identifies 11 factors that affect a horse's
performance in a race. Each of the factors is given a percentage
value, which may be modified by the user. Frequent changing of the
Factors' values should, however, be avoided. The defaults do seem to
work well with open & welter type handicaps. (* see 'PREFERENCES' for
more information on the factors *)


Once the details of the race and the horses starting in it have been
entered the ratings can be calculated. The results are shown as
'percent' which makes it easy to work out the 'price' for a particular horse.

Bookies prices are based on percentages. For example

        6/4 = 40%
        2/1 = 33%
        3/1 = 25%

and so on. To convert a percentage figure to odds you can use the formula

    (100/ rating) -1.

For example, 40% evaluates as
                 (100/40) = 2.5.
                2.5 - 1   = 1.5

                1.5 = 6/4

Punters often talk about 'value'. Value in punting is being able to
lay a bet at better odds than the punter's estimation. If the punter
reckons a horse should be at 2/1 and he is able to back it at 3/1 than
he has obtained value.

