            EDITING IN THE PREFERENCE WINDOW

If you want to change the factor values, bring up 'PREFERENCES' from
the PROJECT MENU'. The current preferences are displayed.

Use the mouse to select the  field you want to edit . Change its
value and press [RETURN]. Note the cursor jumps to the next field.

You may also press RIGHT AMIGA & 'E' which places the cursor in the
first field.

If you change the Factors, try to get the total displayed at the
bottom of the screen to show around 100%.


                  THE FACTORS.

The value assigned to each factor is the percentage effect we reckon
it will have on the result of each horse in the race. The descriptions
given to each factor, which AMIGAPUNT links back to other information
you supply about each horse can be expanded as

FITNESS     How fit is the horse? Is it near a win? Has it been
        racing too long? Has it just returned from a spell?

        Calculated from the number of starts since a spell 
        and the lengths behind the winner at the most recent 
        starts.

QUALITY     How good is the horse? A horse that runs and does well
        in quality races is (obviously) better than your
        progressive handicap hack a Kembla Grange on
        a wet Tuesday in June.

        Calculated from the total earnings measured against
        the total starts for a given horse.


CONSISTENCY Strike Rate! How often, and how consistently, does 
        the horse win. The better the ratio of win against starts
        the more consistent the horse.

        Adjustment are made to counter the following:

        Horse A   10 starts 1 win- strike rate = 10%

        Horse B  100 starts 10 wins- strike rate = 10%

        Most punters will argue that horse B is more consistent
        as horse A lacks the experience of B.

        AMIGAPUNT makes adjustments in these cases.


WEIGHT      Horses carrying heavy weights are seen as disadvantaged
        against their lesser weighted competitors.

JOCKEY:     How much influence does the jockey have on the result
        of the race? Eight percent? 20  percent.

        I'll leave it to you to ponder this one.

BARRIER:    Horses outside a given barrier will be disadvantaged.

DISTANCE & TRACK suitability should be self explanatory.

GOING       Is the state of the track and its effect. E.G.
        Good, Slow etc.

SEX     Are Fillies & Mares unreliable? In mixed company
        the defaults are set at 5%.

AGE     AMIGAPUNT penalises young and old horses.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

If you change the Factors you can save them. AMIGAPUNT saves them in
the S: directory as 'APUNT.CONF'

Note that if you save a race the current preferences are saved with
it and loaded back in when the race is recalled.

That way races may have different factors applied to them.


