            EDITING THE RACE CARD

At the top of the RACE CARD DISPLAY are SIX fields into which you
should enter the

DATE for the race, Where the race track is (ROSEHILL, MOONEE VALLEY
etc), the state, the distance of the race, the number of starters and
the weight limit for the race.

When you enter the number of starters, (the number of horses to go around)
that number of numbered lines will appear at the right hand side. 
More about these later.

At the left of the screen is another field marked 'BARRIER PEN.'. Some
barriers, given track and distance, are regarded as being
disadvantageous. You must enter the appropriate barrier into this
field. All barriers beyond and including the one entered will then
calculated as having a negative effect.

If no barriers are disadvantaged enter a number greater than the
number of starters in the race.

Finally click the gadget at the bottom of the left hand side (MARKED
'TRACK COND' ) until you see the  condition best to reflect the state
of the track. (FAST,GOOD,DEAD,SLOW,HEAVY).

