            SELECTING A HORSE.

You are now ready to enter the all important information about each
horse. On the RACE CARD DISPLAY select the number or name of the horse
displayed at the right. DO this by moving the mouse pointer over the
desire horse and clicking the left mouse button.

The HORSE DATA DISPLAY should appear.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

        Entering/ Editing the Horse Data.

Press RIGHT AMIGA & E to place the cursor in the first field ready for 
editing. Hit RETURN after each entry. The cursor moves to the next field.

The fields are:

TAB NUMBER: The number of the Horse. When you first create a new
        race AMIGAPUNT supplies the numbers. Feel free to edit 
        them so they reflect the actual race.

        For example, races with scratchings will have numbers 
        missing.

NAME OF HORSE:  
        Self explanatory!

AGE OF HORSE :  
        In Years! If the form guide says 'AGED' use 7.

WEIGHT TO CARRY: 
        The weight allocated the horse by the Handicapper. 
        Do not deduct apprentice claims.

BARRIER NUMBER: 
        The number of the barrier the horse will start from.

EARNINGS IN DOLLARS:
        The prize money the horse has won.

NUMBER OF STARTS: 
        Self Explanatory.

NUMBER OF WINS:
        DITTO!

JOCKEY'S RATING:
        Tricky,this! Use high values for good jockeys, low for poor.
        For example you could use

        1   For unproven apprentice riders

        2   For ordinary jockeys

        3   For good jockeys 

        4   For exceptional jockeys.


        Or you could use the WIN/STARTS ratios provided by
        some form guides.

SINCE SPELL:
        The number of starts this horse has had since a spell.
        Numbers > 5 are reset to five.

In the following five boxes you should enter the lengths the horse was
beaten by at each of its previous starts. 

SPECIAL NOTE:
        IF, FOR EXAMPLE, YOU INDICATE THE HORSE HAS HAD THREE
        STARTS SINCE A SPELL, THEN YOU MUST ONLY FILL THE TOP
        THREE FIELDS WITH LENGTHS BEATEN. 

        START WITH THE EARLIEST RUN IN THE TOP FIELD AND WORK DOWN
        FROM THERE. 

        THE MOST RECENT START SHOULD THEN BE AT THE BOTTOM OF THE
        LIST.

